4
00:00:06,660 --> 00:00:09,980
Viewer discretion is advised.

5
00:00:10,020 --> 00:00:12,620
[North Star Entertainment]

6
00:00:26,180 --> 00:00:32,220
♫I never know what love is like♫

7
00:00:32,220 --> 00:00:37,020
♫All my life, never once have I experienced it♫

8
00:00:37,020 --> 00:00:40,340
♫No one to take that place in my heart♫

9
00:00:41,580 --> 00:00:47,580
♫But now that I’ve met you, my heart begins to glow♫

10
00:00:47,580 --> 00:00:52,340
♫What feeling is this? Why is my heart fluttering?♫

11
00:00:52,340 --> 00:00:56,460
♫And I just can’t control it.♫

12
00:00:56,460 --> 00:01:00,300
♫What happened to my heart right now?♫

13
00:01:00,300 --> 00:01:04,140
♫I can’t control it when you’re around♫

14
00:01:04,140 --> 00:01:10,300
♫This heart…it stops at you♫

15
00:01:11,140 --> 00:01:15,340
♫ Is this love? Is that what they call it?♫

16
00:01:15,340 --> 00:01:18,740
♫ When my heart starts to waver♫

17
00:01:18,740 --> 00:01:23,380
♫ Like a stream of water slowly pouring over my heart♫

18
00:01:23,380 --> 00:01:26,460
♫ From dusk till dawn, you’re never far from my sight♫

19
00:01:26,460 --> 00:01:30,860
♫ Or is this love? Are you that someone...♫

20
00:01:30,860 --> 00:01:34,340
♫ ...who’s destined to be with me?♫

21
00:01:34,340 --> 00:01:40,500
♫ Is this really happening ? I really want to know ♫

22
00:01:40,500 --> 00:01:41,740
♫‘Cos you now hold a special place in my heart♫

23
00:01:41,740 --> 00:01:46,420
[Waves of Deception]
♫‘Cos you now hold a special place in my heart♫

24
00:01:47,560 --> 00:01:49,729
[Previously]
[Lada]: It was Big Boss who arranged everything, wasn’t it?

25
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:51,500
[Apo]: Can I have the flowers back?

26
00:01:51,759 --> 00:01:53,360
[Lada]: Why would you throw them away?

27
00:01:53,530 --> 00:01:55,650
[Apo]: Those flowers yesterday weren't from me.

28
00:01:55,650 --> 00:01:57,280
So, I bought you one today.

29
00:01:57,300 --> 00:02:00,960
[Pheempat]: I also want to know what she’d say when she finds out you’re my sister.

30
00:02:01,330 --> 00:02:02,130
[Lada]: Look out, Boss!

31
00:02:03,330 --> 00:02:05,980
[Apo]: No matter what happens, I will never leave you.

32
00:02:05,980 --> 00:02:07,480
We’ll go through it together.

33
00:02:07,530 --> 00:02:11,300
[Apo]: I think your heart and mine are now beating as one.

34
00:02:12,300 --> 00:02:15,180
[Apo]: Can you be my girlfriend, Chonlada?

35
00:02:15,730 --> 00:02:19,329
[Adisorn]: Welcome to the Watinwanich family.

36
00:02:19,500 --> 00:02:21,250
[Lada]: Can you guess what I wrote?

37
00:02:21,250 --> 00:02:22,579
[Apo]: Lada.

38
00:02:22,600 --> 00:02:27,130
[Lada]: I never thought hearing you calling my name like that would make me feel so complete.

39
00:02:31,730 --> 00:02:33,260
Who the hell do you think you are?

40
00:02:33,860 --> 00:02:37,050
Who do you think make my company in this f***ing red?

41
00:02:37,329 --> 00:02:38,329
It’s you!

42
00:02:39,260 --> 00:02:40,460
I didn’t order you, Dad.

43
00:02:41,100 --> 00:02:43,360
I was only asking you to cancel your plan to sell off my hotel.

44
00:02:44,160 --> 00:02:46,460
Do you know how much work I’ve put into it?

45
00:02:46,530 --> 00:02:48,300
You can’t just sell it off like this.

46
00:02:49,700 --> 00:02:51,930
It’s not like you’re making any profit from it.

47
00:02:52,800 --> 00:02:54,360
Your hotel is in a crisis, Pat.

48
00:02:54,900 --> 00:02:58,200
Dad is doing this to save the Wachara Group.

49
00:02:58,860 --> 00:03:00,800
In the end, it will eventually affect our major branches.

50
00:03:01,460 --> 00:03:04,080
He has to get rid of whatever is useless.

51
00:03:05,200 --> 00:03:06,080
Who asked you?

52
00:03:07,800 --> 00:03:10,180
You’re just a sister-in-law, don’t butt in.

53
00:03:10,260 --> 00:03:11,330
It’s you who has to stop!

54
00:03:12,160 --> 00:03:14,760
Try to open your damn eyes and ears.

55
00:03:15,400 --> 00:03:18,000
Our business is crashing so low because of whom?

56
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:20,060
We’re all screwed!

57
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:23,780
Dad.

58
00:03:24,710 --> 00:03:26,350
Please give me one last chance.

59
00:03:26,950 --> 00:03:30,050
The auction for the Travel Thailand project is coming soon.

60
00:03:30,050 --> 00:03:31,610
I’ll get you that project.

61
00:03:33,780 --> 00:03:35,780
[Sender: Monarch Global International]

62
00:03:35,780 --> 00:03:38,850
[Proposal and Price Quotation for Tourism Stimulus Project by Tourism Authority of Thailand]

63
00:03:50,460 --> 00:03:55,350
But usually, the Watin Group always ends up getting a big project like that.

64
00:03:55,800 --> 00:03:57,450
But if I can get this project,

65
00:03:59,810 --> 00:04:01,750
will you change your mind about my hotel?

66
00:04:21,050 --> 00:04:22,180
Pat.

67
00:04:26,330 --> 00:04:28,000
What? You wanna talk about that day?

68
00:04:32,260 --> 00:04:34,010
So, you’re not going to help me.

69
00:04:34,260 --> 00:04:36,100
And insist you’ll stay on her side, right?

70
00:04:37,560 --> 00:04:39,400
Then, let me tell you something.

71
00:04:40,060 --> 00:04:42,360
Before you’d say no to me, you’d better hear what Dad would say first.

72
00:04:42,930 --> 00:04:45,010
I heard he has something to talk to you.

73
00:04:45,960 --> 00:04:46,950
What is it?

74
00:04:48,800 --> 00:04:53,600
Lada, make sure you’re free next weekend.

75
00:05:03,760 --> 00:05:07,550
Dad, I have to work on Saturday.

76
00:05:08,380 --> 00:05:12,550
Your mum already told me you’re working for a small company in the upcountry.

77
00:05:13,130 --> 00:05:19,680
You’d better go tell them you’ll quit, because I’m going to introduce you to Kirk, Mr. Huad’s son.

78
00:05:21,860 --> 00:05:23,250
But I’m not free.

79
00:05:28,730 --> 00:05:30,210
Then make sure you are.

80
00:05:30,730 --> 00:05:32,650
Try to make yourself useful this time.

81
00:05:32,860 --> 00:05:35,780
Don’t you think you should at least help the Wachara group somehow?

82
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:43,310
Your job is to make Kirk fall for you and propose to you.

83
00:05:45,560 --> 00:05:46,650
Dad!

84
00:06:02,560 --> 00:06:04,680
Pat! Pat!

85
00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:08,960
Don’t tell me you have nothing to do with this.

86
00:06:10,860 --> 00:06:11,910
With what?

87
00:06:13,100 --> 00:06:15,060
That Dad will marry you off?

88
00:06:16,960 --> 00:06:18,080
Lada.

89
00:06:18,480 --> 00:06:21,550
You already know, to him, that’s all what a daughter is worth.

90
00:06:23,900 --> 00:06:27,110
I think I know now why you can’t run a hotel.

91
00:06:27,900 --> 00:06:29,510
It’s not because you’re not smart.

92
00:06:30,360 --> 00:06:32,110
But rather because you’re a loser.

93
00:06:32,700 --> 00:06:34,200
You can’t fight like a man.

94
00:06:35,060 --> 00:06:37,510
You use all the dirty tricks just to beat a girl.

95
00:06:38,730 --> 00:06:40,980
But despite doing that,

96
00:06:41,500 --> 00:06:43,460
you still lose to Miss Apo.

97
00:06:44,000 --> 00:06:46,350
It’s all your fault that everything has turned out like this!

98
00:06:46,930 --> 00:06:49,480
If you had done as I said, my hotel would never end up like th

99
00:06:50,860 --> 00:06:53,380
But since you didn’t, I have to find another way out.

100
00:06:54,100 --> 00:06:58,159
I need someone to help fund the Wachara Group and keep it running without being indebted, do you f***ing hear me?

101
00:07:00,530 --> 00:07:04,710
So, you told Dad to marry me off?

102
00:07:06,060 --> 00:07:07,980
I’m not asking you to help me.

103
00:07:07,980 --> 00:07:09,850
I’m actually helping you.

104
00:07:10,480 --> 00:07:15,050
If I can save my hotel, it means you’ll also be saved from this arranged marriage.

105
00:07:16,560 --> 00:07:21,450
And you can also keep your secret from Dad, that you’re in love with a woman.

106
00:07:24,600 --> 00:07:27,280
Have you ever seen me as your sister?

107
00:07:31,200 --> 00:07:33,250
Why are you so cruel?

108
00:07:33,250 --> 00:07:35,880
If that woman finds out who you really are and that,

109
00:07:35,880 --> 00:07:37,909
you’re only working there just to use her,

110
00:07:37,909 --> 00:07:39,450
do you think she’ll still love you?

111
00:07:43,400 --> 00:07:45,000
Use your love as an advantage.

112
00:07:47,900 --> 00:07:50,409
I’ll be waiting for their bidding figure from you.

113
00:08:31,460 --> 00:08:32,450
Lada.

114
00:08:35,309 --> 00:08:38,049
Your family still doesn’t accept me, does they?

115
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:41,850
How did you know?

116
00:08:44,850 --> 00:08:47,050
Since you came back,

117
00:08:47,460 --> 00:08:49,260
I’ve noticed there’s something off about you.

118
00:08:51,500 --> 00:08:53,710
I’m only concerned about something at home.

119
00:08:54,060 --> 00:08:55,380
It’s not about you at all.

120
00:08:58,460 --> 00:09:01,810
I heard Miss Preem said you’re taking next Saturday off to go home.

121
00:09:02,280 --> 00:09:05,710
I also have to be in Bangkok that day, do you need a ride?

122
00:09:06,060 --> 00:09:06,860
It’s okay.

123
00:09:07,500 --> 00:09:11,050
There, it’s really about me.

124
00:09:13,930 --> 00:09:16,730
Have you told your family about me?

125
00:09:19,450 --> 00:09:23,800
My dad is quite conservative.

126
00:09:25,130 --> 00:09:26,880
But I believe that

127
00:09:27,500 --> 00:09:29,750
once he gets to know you,

128
00:09:30,200 --> 00:09:32,100
he’ll surely be fond of you.

129
00:09:35,060 --> 00:09:38,100
But if you don’t want to waste your time waiting for me,

130
00:09:38,760 --> 00:09:39,730
I’d understand.

131
00:09:41,060 --> 00:09:42,360
I’m serious, Lada.

132
00:09:49,130 --> 00:09:52,450
What if there is no future for our relationship?

133
00:09:53,930 --> 00:09:57,880
Don’t worry. I’ll do anything

134
00:09:59,280 --> 00:10:02,510
and will never let you face the problems alone.

135
00:10:06,860 --> 00:10:10,450
I’m so lucky to be your girlfriend.

136
00:10:12,660 --> 00:10:16,610
Well, I’m right here. I promise I won’t go anywhere.

137
00:10:17,550 --> 00:10:19,180
We’ll go through it together.

138
00:10:40,130 --> 00:10:45,880
Boss, I’ve put an envelope that has a price quotation for the TAT project on your desk.

139
00:10:50,160 --> 00:10:53,180
Don’t worry, I’ll take care of the rest here.

140
00:10:53,550 --> 00:10:55,710
Please get on with your meeting with the client.

141
00:10:58,130 --> 00:10:58,930
Yes, Boss.

142
00:11:04,810 --> 00:11:09,010
Miss Preem, haven’t we submitted the proposal yet?

143
00:11:10,360 --> 00:11:14,650
I’d need Boss to approve of the figure again after she’s back from the meeting. Then, we’ll submit it.

144
00:11:14,650 --> 00:11:16,350
The deadline is this Friday.

145
00:11:16,350 --> 00:11:18,680
I’ll go talk to Miss Wadee first.

146
00:11:18,680 --> 00:11:20,980
You can call me if there’s anything.

147
00:11:21,800 --> 00:11:22,600
Sure.

148
00:12:11,810 --> 00:12:13,780
[Sender: Monarch Global International]

149
00:12:13,780 --> 00:12:17,350
[Proposal and Price Quotation for Tourism Stimulus Project by Tourism Authority of Thailand]

150
00:13:58,600 --> 00:14:01,180
You don’t have to drop me off tomorrow, Nam.

151
00:14:02,330 --> 00:14:03,130
Why?

152
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:05,100
Getting bored of me already?

153
00:14:06,160 --> 00:14:09,750
Don’t say that. It hurts.

154
00:14:10,160 --> 00:14:11,850
How can you accuse me like that?

155
00:14:14,530 --> 00:14:15,650
I was kidding.

156
00:14:16,930 --> 00:14:17,880
Just kidding.

157
00:14:19,460 --> 00:14:21,100
I’m just worried.

158
00:14:21,360 --> 00:14:24,610
You have to look after the resort and the hotel too.

159
00:14:25,800 --> 00:14:27,380
Don’t worry about me.

160
00:14:27,960 --> 00:14:31,210
Spending time with you makes all my tiredness disappear.

161
00:14:32,660 --> 00:14:37,710
But isn’t tomorrow the result announcement date for the TAT project?

162
00:14:39,800 --> 00:14:42,780
Mhm, and it’s also your birthday, isn’t it?

163
00:14:44,500 --> 00:14:45,800
How did you know?

164
00:14:46,760 --> 00:14:50,850
Don’t tell me you sneaked a peek at my resume again.

165
00:14:53,760 --> 00:14:55,910
Where should we celebrate your birthday then?

166
00:14:56,800 --> 00:14:59,180
But it’s the same day as the announcement for the result.

167
00:15:01,960 --> 00:15:03,180
If it were before,

168
00:15:03,180 --> 00:15:05,780
I would’ve put my first priority on work.

169
00:15:06,410 --> 00:15:08,650
But now, I already have something more important.

170
00:15:11,800 --> 00:15:18,360
Then, can you come to my room to celebrate my birthday?

171
00:15:24,300 --> 00:15:26,360
What gift do you want for your birthday?

172
00:15:29,400 --> 00:15:30,750
Nothing.

173
00:15:31,500 --> 00:15:35,680
I already have the most special gift in my life right in front of me.

174
00:15:39,460 --> 00:15:44,880
Then, can I kiss you?

175
00:15:51,000 --> 00:15:52,450
Not here.

176
00:15:53,300 --> 00:15:56,550
Does that mean I can do it somewhere else?

177
00:15:58,350 --> 00:15:59,850
Nam!

178
00:16:02,730 --> 00:16:06,360
Then, don’t look so adorable. I can’t resist it.

179
00:16:09,060 --> 00:16:12,580
So, you’ll come see me after work tomorrow, right?

180
00:16:15,750 --> 00:16:17,850
I’ll take a day off tomorrow then.

181
00:16:18,310 --> 00:16:21,410
No, you can’t. You should get your work done first.

182
00:16:21,980 --> 00:16:24,610
Don’t ever let love ruin your work.

183
00:16:28,710 --> 00:16:32,910
No hurry. I can wait.

184
00:16:34,300 --> 00:16:35,250
Why?

185
00:16:37,130 --> 00:16:39,000
Are you going to confess your love to me?

186
00:16:41,100 --> 00:16:45,310
Tomorrow, I’ll empty my heart out.

187
00:16:45,800 --> 00:16:48,550
I’ll confess everything to you.

188
00:17:04,099 --> 00:17:05,260
Miss Chonlada!

189
00:17:06,099 --> 00:17:07,099
Miss Chonlada.

190
00:17:08,130 --> 00:17:09,010
Preem.

191
00:17:10,730 --> 00:17:12,180
The result is out.

192
00:17:13,500 --> 00:17:15,079
Who won?

193
00:17:23,700 --> 00:17:25,550
Why don’t you take this call first?

194
00:17:27,109 --> 00:17:28,180
Excuse me then.

195
00:17:44,160 --> 00:17:45,250
Hello, Pat.

196
00:17:45,460 --> 00:17:47,180
In the end, you chose to betray me.

197
00:17:49,130 --> 00:17:52,010
But I already sent you the figure.

198
00:17:52,100 --> 00:17:54,910
That’s not the amount the Watin Group proposed for the bidding!

199
00:17:59,530 --> 00:18:01,180
You chose this path yourself.

200
00:18:04,780 --> 00:18:06,050
Pat!

201
00:18:17,900 --> 00:18:18,950
Fighting.

202
00:18:19,400 --> 00:18:20,330
Miss Preem.

203
00:18:20,530 --> 00:18:22,550
Where is Boss having a meeting?

204
00:18:22,930 --> 00:18:24,330
A convention centre near our hotel.

205
00:18:24,460 --> 00:18:25,510
Is there something wrong?

206
00:18:25,600 --> 00:18:26,510
Thank you!

207
00:18:27,060 --> 00:18:29,000
Huh? Miss Chonlada!

208
00:19:03,100 --> 00:19:05,110
It’s the Watin Group again.

209
00:19:11,580 --> 00:19:14,410
Can you go faster?

210
00:19:15,060 --> 00:19:16,350
Just get ahead of them.

211
00:19:20,900 --> 00:19:22,650
Congratulations indeed.

212
00:19:23,660 --> 00:19:26,350
And also sorry about Chonlada.

213
00:19:29,100 --> 00:19:29,930
Chonlada?

214
00:19:31,500 --> 00:19:32,730
Why? What’s wrong with her?

215
00:19:36,160 --> 00:19:38,280
Listen to me carefully, Miss Apo.

216
00:19:39,500 --> 00:19:41,580
I’ll tell you all the truth

217
00:19:42,330 --> 00:19:45,400
Because I can’t stand watching you acting like a fool any longer.

218
00:19:53,000 --> 00:19:54,910
Chonlada is my little sister.

219
00:20:05,860 --> 00:20:07,310
Can you tell me where the convention hall is?

220
00:20:08,260 --> 00:20:09,150
Upstairs?

221
00:20:20,730 --> 00:20:23,200
You have absolutely no idea she’s my sister, don’t you?

222
00:20:25,500 --> 00:20:27,760
I also didn’t expect my sister

223
00:20:28,660 --> 00:20:31,250
to be able to make a so-called talented and astute person like you,

224
00:20:31,250 --> 00:20:33,680
fall head over heels for her.

225
00:20:35,360 --> 00:20:37,710
You probably love her so much, don’t you?

226
00:20:40,930 --> 00:20:42,380
Have I ever said

227
00:20:43,760 --> 00:20:45,550
that I love Chonlada?

228
00:20:47,200 --> 00:20:48,910
It must have hurt terribly

229
00:20:49,100 --> 00:20:50,760
to be betrayed by the person you love.

230
00:20:52,730 --> 00:20:59,280
I think the one who has been betrayed is rather you, Mr. Pheempat.

231
00:21:01,000 --> 00:21:01,860
What do you mean?

232
00:21:04,400 --> 00:21:08,780
Do you really think I don’t know who Chonlada is?

233
00:21:11,860 --> 00:21:14,650
I’ve known it since the very first day I met your sister.

234
00:21:27,100 --> 00:21:29,310
Hey, watch where you’re going!

235
00:21:31,300 --> 00:21:33,500
Here’s the contact info of that guest.

236
00:21:35,260 --> 00:21:37,880
I’ll take care of your phone as soon as possible.

237
00:21:40,000 --> 00:21:41,350
That’s why she looks so familiar.
[Welcome to ‘Talk With The Millionaire’,]

238
00:21:41,350 --> 00:21:43,410
[Welcome to ‘Talk With The Millionaire’,]

239
00:21:43,410 --> 00:21:44,710
[the show that will tell you about visions and success of the most powerful moguls in our country.]

240
00:21:44,710 --> 00:21:45,650
Who looks familiar, Boss?
[the show that will tell you about visions and success of the most powerful moguls in our country.]

241
00:21:45,650 --> 00:21:51,310
[the show that will tell you about visions and success of the most powerful moguls in our country.]

242
00:21:55,930 --> 00:21:57,580
At first, I wasn’t quite sure.

243
00:21:58,160 --> 00:22:01,750
But I often watch this interview clip.

244
00:22:02,330 --> 00:22:06,350
After rechecking it, I’m sure she’s someone from Mr. Pheemdet’s family.

245
00:22:07,600 --> 00:22:11,110
Or she might just be someone who works at Mr. Pheemdet’s house.

246
00:22:11,400 --> 00:22:13,450
This show was aired two weeks ago.

247
00:22:14,130 --> 00:22:17,510
That means this woman is still working at Mr. Pheemdet’s house.

248
00:22:18,530 --> 00:22:21,050
Suppose someone from the Wachara Group is here for a vacation.

249
00:22:21,330 --> 00:22:23,650
Then, why didn’t they stay at the Wachara Group’s hotel?

250
00:22:23,900 --> 00:22:26,280
Why would they choose to stay at our hotel who’s their rival?

251
00:22:26,960 --> 00:22:28,650
Don’t you think it’s strange?

252
00:22:29,860 --> 00:22:31,930
Do you want me to look further into it, Boss?

253
00:22:41,260 --> 00:22:48,250
And then, you played right into my hands by sending your sister to me.

254
00:22:54,260 --> 00:22:59,250
Boss, are you sure you want to hire someone from the Wachara Group?

255
00:23:00,700 --> 00:23:02,510
She came to stay at our hotel.

256
00:23:03,700 --> 00:23:05,710
And even applied for a job here.

257
00:23:06,200 --> 00:23:07,950
I don’t think it’s just a coincidence.

258
00:23:09,360 --> 00:23:10,850
For now, just play along.

259
00:23:11,600 --> 00:23:14,360
Try to find out why the Wachara Group sent this girl to work with us.

260
00:23:20,000 --> 00:23:27,010
I admit that at first I didn’t know how Chonlada is related to the Wachara Group.

261
00:23:28,900 --> 00:23:34,410
But it was you who gave me the answer.

262
00:23:36,100 --> 00:23:38,780
Miss Chonlada is Mr. Pheemdet’s daughter.

263
00:23:40,500 --> 00:23:42,500
You did a background check on her?

264
00:23:44,930 --> 00:23:48,150
Well, it’s because you seem to be interested in her.

265
00:23:48,910 --> 00:23:49,950
Stop.

266
00:23:50,760 --> 00:23:53,400
You can deny it all you want.

267
00:23:53,760 --> 00:23:57,350
But I still want to know who she is. So, I just…

268
00:23:59,260 --> 00:24:00,060
Look into her.

269
00:24:07,200 --> 00:24:08,910
I’ve never heard it before

270
00:24:09,730 --> 00:24:12,180
that Mr. Pheemdet also has a daughter.

271
00:24:14,100 --> 00:24:19,250
I only know he has two sons who are helping him run the family business.

272
00:24:20,730 --> 00:24:22,660
That’s because Miss Chonlada is an illegitimate child.

273
00:24:22,930 --> 00:24:24,910
Mr. Pheemdet has never revealed it to anyone.

274
00:24:26,600 --> 00:24:28,850
She uses her mother’s surname.

275
00:24:29,350 --> 00:24:31,180
She uses her mother’s surname.

276
00:24:31,180 --> 00:24:33,580
That’s the only proof she’s his daughter.

277
00:24:36,330 --> 00:24:41,350
This means Mr. Pheemdet has sent Chonladad to work with the Watin Group

278
00:24:43,900 --> 00:24:45,930
because he thinks no one knows she’s his daughter.

279
00:24:47,700 --> 00:24:50,080
I don’t know who it is that sent her.

280
00:24:50,400 --> 00:24:51,710
But after I found out

281
00:24:51,710 --> 00:24:54,150
that she’s Mr. Pheemdet’s daughter,

282
00:24:54,260 --> 00:24:56,710
I decided to keep an eye on her to find out what she’s up to.

283
00:24:57,160 --> 00:25:00,010
Then, I saw Mr. Pheempat at her condo.

284
00:25:15,530 --> 00:25:17,730
As I thought, my sister is really good for nothing.

285
00:25:21,760 --> 00:25:23,750
Apart from Apo,

286
00:25:24,300 --> 00:25:25,900
keep an eye on Lada for me too.

287
00:25:27,200 --> 00:25:28,000
Yes.

288
00:25:41,130 --> 00:25:42,550
What else have you found?

289
00:25:44,100 --> 00:25:49,810
That’s all I have. So, I decided to talk to those who know Miss Chonalda.

290
00:25:49,810 --> 00:25:52,080
Whether it’s her college friends,

291
00:25:52,510 --> 00:25:55,450
or the maids in her house, they all said the same thing.

292
00:25:55,450 --> 00:25:59,750
That, unlike his sons, Mr. Pheemdet hardly gives his daughter a chance to voice out.

293
00:26:00,960 --> 00:26:06,680
Are you saying that Chonlada applied to work at the Watin Group

294
00:26:06,680 --> 00:26:10,950
because Pheempat has tricked her into doing it to prove herself to her family?

295
00:26:13,530 --> 00:26:17,850
When I knew that, do you know what I did next?

296
00:26:26,260 --> 00:26:27,850
Go home and rest, Miss Preem.

297
00:26:28,360 --> 00:26:29,530
Don’t worry about work.

298
00:26:29,730 --> 00:26:31,500
I’ll have Chonlada take care of it.

299
00:26:33,960 --> 00:26:37,350
Once you get better,

300
00:26:38,060 --> 00:26:41,210
please find me a hotel staff that we can trust

301
00:26:41,900 --> 00:26:45,080
and tell them to keep an eye on an employee called Maythawee.

302
00:26:46,660 --> 00:26:49,210
Are you here to talk about that?

303
00:26:52,600 --> 00:26:55,710
Mr. Pheempat brought Miss Chonlada’s mother to her condo.

304
00:26:56,160 --> 00:26:56,960
That’s right.

305
00:26:57,500 --> 00:27:00,450
Now I remember, I used to talk someone who knows Miss Chonlada.

306
00:27:00,900 --> 00:27:04,710
That person said Miss Chonlada is so scared of her father.

307
00:27:05,860 --> 00:27:09,210
But she loves her mother a lot though.

308
00:27:11,260 --> 00:27:17,660
So, you think Pheempat is using Chonlada’s mother to threaten her to do something, right?

309
00:27:19,200 --> 00:27:22,280
Chef Ian’s opening event is in a few days, isn’t it?

310
00:28:00,160 --> 00:28:04,850
Sis, Miss Chonlada has tampered with Chef Ian’s ingredients.

311
00:28:05,400 --> 00:28:07,810
But after I saw her dump it into the sink,

312
00:28:07,900 --> 00:28:10,010
I rushed out to look for Miss Maythawee.

313
00:28:10,060 --> 00:28:11,450
But she was still at the party.

314
00:28:13,260 --> 00:28:15,760
Pheempat might have asked someone else to do it.

315
00:28:18,060 --> 00:28:22,810
Maybe he can sense that Miss Chonlada is leaning towards you.

316
00:28:23,180 --> 00:28:25,350
So, he has prepared someone else as a backup plan.

317
00:28:25,680 --> 00:28:27,810
I’m starting to worry about Miss Chonlada.

318
00:28:30,500 --> 00:28:32,160
What do you think Pheempat would do?

319
00:28:38,400 --> 00:28:40,550
That incident at Chef Ian’s opening,

320
00:28:41,860 --> 00:28:43,110
I miscalculated it.

321
00:28:43,660 --> 00:28:46,180
But it was a good lesson learnt that

322
00:28:46,500 --> 00:28:49,510
I should never let your sister out of my sight,

323
00:28:50,860 --> 00:28:52,480
even when I’m not feeling well.

324
00:29:00,460 --> 00:29:02,250
I don’t have feelings for you.

325
00:29:03,130 --> 00:29:05,210
Then why,

326
00:29:06,160 --> 00:29:09,050
aren’t you wearing that smart watch I gave you?

327
00:29:09,700 --> 00:29:11,180
Calm down, Sis.

328
00:29:11,910 --> 00:29:15,480
If Miss Chonlada refuses to wear it, isn’t it obvious that,

329
00:29:15,480 --> 00:29:17,680
she definitely feels something for you?

330
00:29:23,660 --> 00:29:25,910
Do you still remember what I told you?

331
00:29:27,930 --> 00:29:34,280
That if Mr. Pheempat can’t use Chonlada’s mother to threaten her to poison the food,

332
00:29:36,400 --> 00:29:39,380
he might use other ways.

333
00:29:41,260 --> 00:29:42,060
Pat!

334
00:29:43,330 --> 00:29:45,130
I know you’re around here!

335
00:29:45,860 --> 00:29:48,130
No matter how much you’ll threaten me, I won’t be afraid anymore!

336
00:29:50,860 --> 00:29:53,750
I’m going to tell Miss Apo everything and put an end to this lie!

337
00:29:54,860 --> 00:29:57,580
Do you think she’ll still accept you if she knows the truth?

338
00:29:58,300 --> 00:29:59,100
Go on then.

339
00:29:59,960 --> 00:30:03,650
I also want to know what she’d say when she finds out you’re my sister.

340
00:30:04,530 --> 00:30:06,680
Go on and tell her, Chonlada.

341
00:30:07,300 --> 00:30:09,710
Go now. Go!

342
00:30:16,900 --> 00:30:18,680
This figure on the envelope

343
00:30:18,860 --> 00:30:20,860
is the actual amount I had proposed for the auction.

344
00:30:22,730 --> 00:30:25,130
If Chonlada had told you this figure,

345
00:30:26,860 --> 00:30:29,410
I would’ve lost today.

346
00:30:31,400 --> 00:30:35,080
But she intended to tell you the wrong figure.

347
00:30:37,360 --> 00:30:39,350
That’s why I won.

348
00:31:13,900 --> 00:31:15,580
Do you really think that,

349
00:31:16,530 --> 00:31:19,080
your sister can deceive me so easily like that?

350
00:31:21,700 --> 00:31:26,280
It’s rather me who has deceived her.

351
00:31:26,610 --> 00:31:29,680
All I did was playing along.

352
00:31:31,480 --> 00:31:37,280
Because I wanted your sister to trust me and rely on me.

353
00:31:43,160 --> 00:31:45,930
Can you be my girlfriend, Chonlada?

354
00:31:54,400 --> 00:31:58,710
If I were you, I would have felt so devastated.

355
00:31:59,380 --> 00:32:08,250
That my own sister has betrayed me and chosen to protect my rival instead.

356
00:32:12,960 --> 00:32:16,580
So all this time, you’ve been using my sister

357
00:32:17,800 --> 00:32:19,910
and never felt anything for her?

358
00:32:22,200 --> 00:32:23,980
Well, if you want to play the game,

359
00:32:25,300 --> 00:32:27,850
don’t use your feelings or you’ll get too involved with it.

360
00:32:31,460 --> 00:32:35,950
Thank you for sending her to fall for me.

361
00:32:38,260 --> 00:32:40,650
It makes everything so much easier.

362
00:32:48,400 --> 00:32:50,310
You heard her, right, Lada?

363
00:32:58,760 --> 00:32:59,560
Lada.

364
00:33:00,400 --> 00:33:03,180
Have you seen what it’s like to favour others over your own blood?

365
00:33:04,560 --> 00:33:06,130
Not only did you refuse to help your kin,

366
00:33:06,160 --> 00:33:08,600
you even got fooled into destroying your own family!

367
00:33:51,660 --> 00:33:52,450
Lada!

368
00:34:07,260 --> 00:34:08,510
Chonlada!

369
00:34:51,960 --> 00:34:55,179
Miss Chonlada has just returned her key card a moment ago.

370
00:34:55,679 --> 00:34:58,080
But it’s tipping down outside.

371
00:34:58,080 --> 00:34:59,680
It’s probably hard to get a cab.

372
00:34:59,680 --> 00:35:01,610
She mightn’t have gone far.

373
00:37:26,300 --> 00:37:30,980
Don’t tell me you’ve been sitting in the rain like this since when you called me.

374
00:37:33,800 --> 00:37:36,180
You’re afraid I might fall into my own trap.

375
00:37:37,130 --> 00:37:39,460
But it’s actually her trap I’ve fallen into.

376
00:37:39,930 --> 00:37:41,980
I’m so stupid. I should’ve listened to you.

377
00:37:42,130 --> 00:37:43,750
So stupid.

378
00:37:49,200 --> 00:37:50,000
Lada.

379
00:37:50,900 --> 00:37:51,700
It's hurt.

380
00:37:53,500 --> 00:37:54,300
let’s go home.

381
00:37:55,400 --> 00:37:57,110
This isn’t where you belong.

382
00:38:12,360 --> 00:38:13,710
It's okay.

383
00:39:01,900 --> 00:39:05,350
The ring that Boss has it made-to-order is here.

384
00:39:08,400 --> 00:39:11,280
You want the ring head to look like a tulip flower?

385
00:39:12,860 --> 00:39:16,580
Can you contact Miss Khemupsorn’s jewelry shop for me?

386
00:39:17,000 --> 00:39:21,550
Please ask her if there’s any jeweller who can finish this job before next Friday.

387
00:39:24,260 --> 00:39:26,150
Why so hurry, Boss?

388
00:39:26,500 --> 00:39:28,780
Whom are you going to give it to?

389
00:39:34,330 --> 00:39:39,810
Next Friday is Miss Chonlada’s birthday, isn’t it?

390
00:39:41,660 --> 00:39:43,210
Please don’t tell her.

391
00:39:45,700 --> 00:39:51,550
I get it. You want it to be a surprise. Roger that, Boss.

392
00:40:55,360 --> 00:40:57,080
Eat something first.

393
00:41:03,730 --> 00:41:05,080
I’m such an idiot.

394
00:41:08,130 --> 00:41:11,330
Hey, you’re not an idiot.

395
00:41:16,460 --> 00:41:18,200
If I could turn back time,

396
00:41:22,260 --> 00:41:23,810
I would choose to trust you.

397
00:41:26,660 --> 00:41:28,850
I wouldn't agree to help my brother.

398
00:41:30,000 --> 00:41:32,650
I wouldn’t visit the Watin Group’s hotel.

399
00:41:34,930 --> 00:41:36,930
I wouldn’t find excuses to see her.

400
00:41:43,130 --> 00:41:47,410
And I would never ever…fall for her.

401
00:41:57,360 --> 00:41:59,880
Come on, stop thinking about it.

402
00:42:00,580 --> 00:42:02,350
It’s your birthday today.

403
00:42:02,880 --> 00:42:09,350
They say if you’re sad on your birthday, you’ll be sad for the rest of the year.

404
00:42:15,160 --> 00:42:17,060
I guess I’ll be sad forever.

405
00:42:26,560 --> 00:42:32,210
Nate, can I stay with you for a few more days?

406
00:42:33,460 --> 00:42:35,650
I don’t want to go home right now.

407
00:42:37,360 --> 00:42:39,110
You can stay as long as you want.

408
00:42:39,550 --> 00:42:42,210
Let’s figure it out when you feel better.

409
00:42:42,850 --> 00:42:43,910
Okay?

410
00:42:45,500 --> 00:42:46,300
Thank you.

411
00:43:53,360 --> 00:43:55,010
Happy Birthday, pal.

412
00:44:10,930 --> 00:44:16,180
At least on a crappy day like this, I still have you.

413
00:44:19,100 --> 00:44:20,100
Make a wish.

414
00:44:29,730 --> 00:44:33,310
May I never experience pain in love ever again.

415
00:44:35,000 --> 00:44:36,730
May I never fall in love with anyone again.

416
00:44:55,530 --> 00:44:58,010
May you find only happiness from now on.

417
00:46:18,010 --> 00:46:19,180
Nam.

418
00:46:29,150 --> 00:46:30,680
Dad.

419
00:46:34,360 --> 00:46:36,160
Can you get hold of Lada?

420
00:46:39,200 --> 00:46:40,680
I didn’t tell him that.

421
00:46:44,800 --> 00:46:48,080
Have you tried looking for her at Mr. Pheemdet’s place?

422
00:46:52,500 --> 00:46:54,310
I didn’t tell him that either.

423
00:46:57,800 --> 00:46:59,980
When did you find out?

424
00:47:02,660 --> 00:47:06,550
Since the Watin Group and the Wachara Group have become rivals.

425
00:47:11,400 --> 00:47:13,010
You knew it all along?

426
00:47:14,660 --> 00:47:16,810
I’ve always known who Lada is.

427
00:47:17,360 --> 00:47:18,710
I know how she grew up.

428
00:47:20,500 --> 00:47:25,150
And I feel so sorry for her that her father values his sons over his daughter.

429
00:47:31,530 --> 00:47:34,710
That’s why I want you to become close to her.

430
00:47:41,900 --> 00:47:45,660
But she is our rival’s daughter, Dad.

431
00:47:48,500 --> 00:47:50,310
But you love her, don’t you?

432
00:47:55,730 --> 00:47:58,950
Because she isn’t like the others from the Wachara Group, isn’t she?

433
00:48:03,200 --> 00:48:05,410
I know what’s going on right now.

434
00:48:06,300 --> 00:48:08,680
But don’t leave it be for too long.

435
00:48:13,860 --> 00:48:17,110
The road to love never runs smooth.

436
00:48:55,600 --> 00:48:59,280
Boss, I told you to sleep in bed, not on the couch.

437
00:49:01,330 --> 00:49:03,310
I’m too tired to argue with you.

438
00:49:03,560 --> 00:49:04,880
Good night then.

439
00:49:07,700 --> 00:49:09,210
Get up, Boss.

440
00:49:09,260 --> 00:49:09,750
No.

441
00:49:09,750 --> 00:49:11,110
-Boss.
- Chonlada.

442
00:49:12,860 --> 00:49:13,660
Get up.

443
00:49:39,660 --> 00:49:44,010
Can I have the smart watch I gave you back?

444
00:49:45,130 --> 00:49:45,960
Why?

445
00:49:48,200 --> 00:49:55,750
I think your heart and mine are now already beating as one.

446
00:50:43,930 --> 00:50:45,580
Just a second, Aunt Mon.

447
00:50:48,700 --> 00:50:50,850
Lada, it’s your mum.

448
00:50:58,730 --> 00:51:03,550
Sweetie, if you’ve already quit your job, why don’t you just come home?

449
00:51:06,930 --> 00:51:08,360
Did Pat tell you?

450
00:51:12,530 --> 00:51:14,550
Are you staying with Nate?

451
00:51:17,100 --> 00:51:20,650
If you’re happy there, you don’t have to come home yet, sweetie.

452
00:51:21,000 --> 00:51:23,110
I told you to tell her to come home!

453
00:51:23,110 --> 00:51:24,650
Why the hell did you tell her otherwise

454
00:51:25,060 --> 00:51:27,350
- Mum? Mum!
- No. Please don’t!

455
00:51:27,350 --> 00:51:29,080
Please answer me, Mum!

456
00:51:29,080 --> 00:51:30,550
Don’t hurt her, Dad!

457
00:51:30,550 --> 00:51:32,650
Damn it! Mum!

458
00:51:33,860 --> 00:51:36,150
I know who you’ve worked for.

459
00:51:36,860 --> 00:51:37,930
How dare you go to work with the bloody Watin Group!

460
00:51:40,900 --> 00:51:45,250
You also disobeyed me and didn’t show up to meet with Mr. Huad’s son.

461
00:51:48,330 --> 00:51:50,550
Get your ass back here right now!

462
00:51:50,900 --> 00:51:55,550
Or else your mother will pay for what you’ve done.

463
00:52:05,000 --> 00:52:07,000
Mum.

464
00:53:15,400 --> 00:53:17,810
Surprise, Mummy!

465
00:53:22,760 --> 00:53:23,510
Lom.

466
00:53:25,700 --> 00:53:27,180
Hello, N

467
00:53:36,560 --> 00:53:41,880
Rose. Din. Fai.

468
00:53:43,860 --> 00:53:46,560
What’s going on? Why are you all here?

469
00:53:48,100 --> 00:53:52,250
Fah sent me an SOS saying that you’re in need of urgent he

470
00:53:52,510 --> 00:53:54,610
So, I called Din and our rascal Fai,

471
00:53:54,610 --> 00:53:57,150
in case you might want to say your last words. We’re all here now.

472
00:53:59,300 --> 00:54:01,050
Geez, don’t exaggerate it.

473
00:54:01,380 --> 00:54:04,310
Just a heartbreak wouldn’t kill you, right?

474
00:54:24,510 --> 00:54:26,200
Give me a hug.

475
00:54:35,330 --> 00:54:37,550
It's will be okay.

476
00:55:07,660 --> 00:55:09,930
Fah already told us briefly what happene

477
00:55:14,400 --> 00:55:17,210
Actually, I’m really not into this kind of stuff.

478
00:55:17,530 --> 00:55:21,410
But if you have a problem, we definitely have to help

479
00:55:23,400 --> 00:55:25,680
It doesn’t matter how smart you are.

480
00:55:26,110 --> 00:55:30,210
Those who are even smarter than you also have no clue when it comes to love.

481
00:55:31,130 --> 00:55:36,650
I agree. I felt so lost and didn’t know what to do back then.

482
00:55:50,500 --> 00:55:52,180
But before we’d help you,

483
00:55:52,360 --> 00:55:54,010
can I rub it in on you first?

484
00:55:54,730 --> 00:55:56,510
You kicked me out of the equatio

485
00:55:56,760 --> 00:55:59,080
And managed to get such a perfect girl as your girlfriend.

486
00:55:59,500 --> 00:56:01,680
But why did you break her heart like that?

487
00:56:04,530 --> 00:56:10,850
Please tell me honestly, do you like her for real or was it just a game for you?

488
00:56:19,000 --> 00:56:20,200
I did like her for real.

489
00:56:22,530 --> 00:56:24,050
But I don’t like her now.

490
00:56:24,960 --> 00:56:25,800
What?

491
00:56:27,960 --> 00:56:28,900
What the heck, Sis?

492
00:56:30,530 --> 00:56:34,950
If you’re going to make up with her just so that you could hurt her again,

493
00:56:35,000 --> 00:56:37,050
- you can count me out. /
- Yeah.

494
00:56:38,800 --> 00:56:44,950
I feel pity for you but if you’re playing with Miss Chonlada’s feelings like this, I’ll pass too.

495
00:56:45,400 --> 00:56:48,780
Hold on, you two. Let her finish talking first.

496
00:56:49,050 --> 00:56:51,380
I think she’s not done yet.

497
00:57:11,760 --> 00:57:12,710
I don’t like her.

498
00:57:14,700 --> 00:57:16,480
But I love her.

499
00:57:18,730 --> 00:57:19,980
So much that

500
00:57:20,730 --> 00:57:22,350
I don’t want to lose her.

501
00:57:28,800 --> 00:57:31,180
Why didn’t you finish it in the first place?

502
00:57:33,160 --> 00:57:35,710
The defendant has made her full confession.

503
00:57:35,900 --> 00:57:38,710
How do you suggest we solve this case, Lieut.?

504
00:57:40,600 --> 00:57:42,810
Now that all of us are here,

505
00:57:43,480 --> 00:57:46,580
the Wachara Group should better be prepared for some chaos.

506
00:58:00,200 --> 00:58:02,780
You can stay with me first, Lada.

507
00:58:02,780 --> 00:58:04,780
Then we can figure this out along the way.

508
00:58:04,780 --> 00:58:06,010
No need to rush.

509
00:58:06,010 --> 00:58:07,710
You already saw what Dad did to Mum.

510
00:58:07,710 --> 00:58:10,880
I can’t just hide and let Mum take all the blame.

511
00:58:11,160 --> 00:58:13,080
But are you sure you can ha

512
00:58:13,080 --> 00:58:15,610
Who knows what lies your brother has told your dad.

513
00:58:16,960 --> 00:58:18,610
No matter what, I have to go back.

514
00:58:19,530 --> 00:58:21,710
I have to go back and face the truth.

515
00:58:32,260 --> 00:58:33,480
Don’t worry.

516
00:58:36,700 --> 00:58:38,310
Best of luck.

517
00:59:29,560 --> 00:59:31,750
Look who finally shows up.

518
00:59:36,460 --> 00:59:39,210
Is it because you know you’ll be disinherited?

519
00:59:42,560 --> 00:59:45,060
I didn’t come back sooner because I had a lot to take care of.

520
00:59:46,860 --> 00:59:48,410
Sounds like an excuse.

521
00:59:50,000 --> 00:59:55,050
I already quit my job. So, I’ll have to live on a share from our family fund like before.

522
00:59:56,660 --> 00:59:58,310
Don’t go anywhere tomorrow.

523
00:59:58,360 --> 01:00:01,610
Dad has invited Mr. Huad and Kirk for dinner at our place.

524
01:00:02,460 --> 01:00:04,910
You’d better not do anything to embarrass Dad aga

525
01:00:05,730 --> 01:00:06,860
Heard you loud and clear.

526
01:00:07,400 --> 01:00:09,110
Does anyone still have anything to order me?

527
01:00:16,200 --> 01:00:17,510
I told you, didn’t I?

528
01:00:17,930 --> 01:00:20,910
That if I can’t save my hotel, you’ll have to take all the blame.

529
01:00:23,400 --> 01:00:25,780
Just think of it as a good deed for your family.

530
01:00:27,130 --> 01:00:29,250
It’s better than letting someone else keep fooling you.

531
01:00:46,730 --> 01:00:48,210
Did Dad do this to you?

532
01:01:00,560 --> 01:01:01,930
It’s okay, dear.

533
01:01:06,560 --> 01:01:07,880
Don’t worry about me.

534
01:01:09,460 --> 01:01:11,050
I’m used to it.

535
01:01:19,100 --> 01:01:24,950
All this time, I’ve been so weak and failed to protect you.

536
01:01:27,730 --> 01:01:33,180
But from now on, whatever he’ll make you do,

537
01:01:34,700 --> 01:01:40,450
you don’t have to do it if you don’t want t

538
01:01:44,160 --> 01:01:52,010
Marriage isn’t something…you can quit so easily.

539
01:02:04,730 --> 01:02:07,860
No matter how far I’d run, he would never leave me be, Mum.

540
01:02:09,800 --> 01:02:11,450
Are you going to give in?

541
01:02:13,360 --> 01:02:18,560
I was born to please everyone and do whatever they say anyway, wasn’t I?

542
01:02:21,300 --> 01:02:23,880
What does it matter if I have to put up with one more demand?

543
01:02:26,730 --> 01:02:27,530
Lada.

544
01:02:30,160 --> 01:02:31,810
I’ll go get some rest first.

545
01:03:30,080 --> 01:03:31,750
I can’t take it anymore.

546
01:03:34,510 --> 01:03:50,480
Lada…it’s all right, sweetie.

547
01:04:24,100 --> 01:04:27,250
[Next Episode]
[Chutimon]: You and Kirk haven’t signed a certificate of marriage yet.

548
01:04:28,060 --> 01:04:30,150
You can still change your mind, dear.

549
01:04:30,660 --> 01:04:32,700
[Lada]: Please trust my decision, Mum.

550
01:04:39,300 --> 01:04:41,250
[Pheempat]: What the f*** is it this time?

551
01:04:41,760 --> 01:04:44,280
Nate : Lada, there’s commotion at the hotel.

552
01:04:45,530 --> 01:04:47,980
[Lom]: The peace ambassador has failed to negotiate.

553
01:04:49,560 --> 01:04:52,410
[Apo]: Leave the rest to me.

554
01:04:55,200 --> 01:04:59,950
[Lada]: Excuse me? These sunflowers and tulips, how much are you selling them?

555
01:05:23,550 --> 01:05:29,080
♫ Since the day you came into my life, I start to realise…♫

556
01:05:29,080 --> 01:05:33,250
♫ What it’s like to be someone who matters ♫

557
01:05:33,250 --> 01:05:39,180
♫ Feeling so warm whenever I see you♫

558
01:05:39,180 --> 01:05:41,950
♫ Who often stays close to me♫

559
01:05:41,950 --> 01:05:46,850
♫ I just want you to know♫

560
01:05:46,850 --> 01:05:53,680
♫ This feeling that’s happening inside♫

561
01:05:53,680 --> 01:05:56,750
♫ I don’t want to hide it anymore♫

562
01:05:56,750 --> 01:06:00,480
♫ I guess I’ll have to tell you♫

563
01:06:01,150 --> 01:06:05,180
♫ You’re the one that change my life ♫

564
01:06:05,910 --> 01:06:10,180
♫ Make me feel more important than anyone♫

565
01:06:10,180 --> 01:06:15,510
♫ Thank you so much for making my life meaningful♫

566
01:06:15,510 --> 01:06:21,850
♫ How lucky I am to have you♫

567
01:06:26,050 --> 01:06:31,850
[Waves of Deception]

